@startuml seq_20_private_messaging
title Sequence Diagram: UC-20 Private Messaging (E2EE)

actor User
participant "User Web (Client)" as Frontend
participant "Crypto Module" as Crypto
participant "Message Controller\n(WebSocket)" as Controller
participant "Message Service" as Service
participant "Message Repo" as Repo
participant "Event Bus\n(Go Channels)" as EventBus

User -> Frontend: Open Messages
Frontend -> Controller: GET /api/messages/channels
Controller -> Service: Get User Channels
Service -> Repo: Find channels for user
Repo --> Service: List of channels
Service --> Controller: Channels Data
Controller --> Frontend: 200 OK (Channels)
Frontend --> User: Display conversations

User -> Frontend: Type message & Send
Frontend -> Crypto: Encrypt message with recipient's Public Key (E2EE)
Crypto --> Frontend: Encrypted Ciphertext
Frontend -> Controller: WS Send {channel_id, ciphertext}
Controller -> Service: Process Message
Service -> Repo: Validate channel membership
Repo --> Service: Membership valid
Service -> Repo: Persist Encrypted Message
Repo --> Service: Message saved
Service -> EventBus: Broadcast to Channel Members
EventBus --> Controller: Push to recipient's WS connection
Controller -> Frontend: WS Deliver Message (Ciphertext)
Frontend -> Crypto: Decrypt with User's Private Key
Crypto --> Frontend: Plaintext Message
Frontend --> User: Display new message
@enduml